main event: A witness reported seeing a bright, circular object in the sky over Philadelphia, Pennsylvania on 25 August 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for a total of 2 minutes,The object was silent and moved very fast,The witness described it as having no glow or flame but appeared to glow,The sighting lasted for approximately 5 seconds according to another source,The object appeared to resemble an inverted saucer with possible lights around the edges.
witness description: The witness described the object as fast-moving and silent, resembling an inverted saucer.
